<inglise> Whereas, besides making provision for the abolition of restrictions, the General Programmes provide that it should be examined whether such abolition should be preceded, accompanied or followed by mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other formal qualifications, and by the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions concerning the taking up and pursuit of the activities in question, and whether, if need be, transitional measures should be adopted pending such recognition or coordination; whereas in addition certain Council Directives concerning the attainment of freedom of establishment and freedom to provide services provide for the adoption of directives concerning mutual recognition as regards activities relating to trade in and distribution of toxic products and activities entailing the professional use of such products; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: lisaks kitsenduste t&uuml;histamise s&auml;testamisele n&auml;evad need &uuml;ldprogrammid ette, et tuleks uurida, kas t&uuml;histamisele peaks eelnema, sellega kaasnema v&otilde;i sellele j&auml;rgnema diplomite, sertifikaatide ja muude kvalifikatsioonitunnistuste vastastikune tunnustamine ning k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste alustamist ja j&auml;tkamist k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamine ning kas vajaduse korral tuleks kuni sellise tunnustamise v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastamiseni vastu v&otilde;tta &uuml;leminekumeetmeid; lisaks n&auml;evad teatavad asutamisvabaduse ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse saavutamist k&auml;sitlevad n&otilde;ukogu direktiivid ette direktiivide vastuv&otilde;tmise, mis k&auml;sitlevad vastastikust tunnustamist toksiliste toodetega kauplemise ja nende vahendamisega seotud ning selliste toodete erialast kasutamist eeldavate tegevuste osas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in particular Council Directive No 64/427/EEC (5) of 7 July 1964 laying down detailed provisions concerning provided measures in respect of activities of self-employed persons in manufacturing and processing industries falling within ISIC Major Groups 23-40 (Industry and small craft industries) and as in Directive No 68/336/EEC (6) of 15 October 1968 laying down detailed provisions concerning provisional measures in respect of activities of self-employed persons in the food manufacturing and beverage industry (ISIC Major Groups 20 and 21) do not exclude the use of toxic products in the pursuit of the activities to which they apply; whereas the transitional measures provided in these Directives are accordingly also applicable to the use of such products where the pursuit of these activities so requires; </inglise>
<eesti> eelk&otilde;ige n&otilde;ukogu 7. juuli 1964. aasta direktiiv nr 64/427/EM&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad &uuml;leminekumeetmete kohta seoses f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate tegutsemisega ISICi p&otilde;higruppide 23-40 alla kuuluva tootmise ja t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise valdkonnas (t&ouml;&ouml;stus ja k&auml;sit&ouml;&ouml;ndus), (5) ja 15. oktoobri 1968. aasta direktiiv 68/336/EM&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad &uuml;leminekumeetmete kohta seoses f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate tegutsemisega toiduaine- ja joogit&ouml;&ouml;stuses (ISICi p&otilde;higrupid 20 ja 21), (6) ei v&auml;lista toksiliste toodete kasutamist seoses tegevuste j&auml;tkamisega, mille suhtes neid kohaldatakse; nendes direktiivides etten&auml;htud &uuml;leminekumeetmeid kohaldatakse vastavalt ka selliste toodete kasutamise suhtes, kui nende tegevuste j&auml;tkamine seda n&otilde;uab; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas for activities relating to trade in and distribution of toxic products and activities entailing the professional use of such products including activities of intermediaries, certain Member States sometimes require persons engaged in any of these activities to possess certain abilities attested by formal qualifications or diplomas, whilst other Member States do not impose any specific requirements but merely subject the handling or storage of toxic products to certain special conditions; whereas it is not therefore possible to effect the coordination provided for at the same time as the abolition of discrimination; whereas such coordination must be effected at a later date; </inglise>
<eesti> toksiliste toodetega kauplemise ja nende vahendamisega seonduvate ning selliste toodete erialast kasutamist eeldavate tegevuste, kaasa arvatud vahendajate tegevuse puhul n&otilde;uavad teatavad liikmesriigid m&otilde;nikord, et k&otilde;igil nende tegevustega seotud isikutel oleksid teatavad kvalifikatsioonitunnistuste v&otilde;i diplomitega t&otilde;endatud oskused, samal ajal kui teised liikmesriigid ei kehtesta konkreetseid n&otilde;udeid, vaid kehtestavad toksiliste toodete k&auml;itlemise v&otilde;i ladustamise kohta &uuml;ksnes teatavad eritingimused; seet&otilde;ttu pole v&otilde;imalik saavutada etten&auml;htud koosk&otilde;lastamist samal ajal kui diskrimineerimise kaotamist; selline koosk&otilde;lastamine tuleb saavutada hiljem; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the absence of immediate coordination, it nevertheless appears desirable to make it easier to attain freedom of establishment and freedom to provide services for the activities in question by the adoption of transitional measures of the kind envisaged in the General Programmes, in particular in order to avoid causing exceptional difficulties for nationals of Member States in which the taking up of such activities is not subject to any conditions; </inglise>
<eesti> otsese koosk&otilde;lastamise puududes tundub siiski soovitavana lihtsustada k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste jaoks asutamisvabaduse ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse saavutamist, v&otilde;ttes vastu &uuml;ldprogrammides kavandatud laadi &uuml;leminekumeetmed eesk&auml;tt selleks, et v&auml;ltida erandlike raskuste p&otilde;hjustamist liikmesriikide kodanikele, kus selliste tegevuste alustamine ei s&otilde;ltu mingitest tingimustest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to prevent such difficulties arising, the main object of the transitional measures should be to allow, as sufficient qualification for taking up the activities in question in host Member States which have rules governing the taking up of such activities, the fact that the activity has been pursued in a Member State of the Community other than the host Member State for a reasonable and sufficiently recent period of time to ensure that the person concerned possesses professional knowledge equivalent to that required of the host Member State's own nationals in view of the dangerous effect which toxic products may have on the health of man, animals and plants either directly or indirectly through the environment; </inglise>
<eesti> selliste raskuste v&auml;ltimiseks peaksid &uuml;leminekumeetmed lubama peamiselt, et k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste alustamiseks vastuv&otilde;tvates liikmesriikides, kellel on selliste tegevuste alustamist reguleerivad eeskirjad, on piisavaks kvalifikatsiooni t&otilde;estuseks asjaolu, et samaga on m&otilde;istliku ja piisavalt hiljutise ajavahemiku jooksul tegeldud &uuml;henduse liikmesriigis, mis pole vastuv&otilde;ttev liikmesriik, mis tagab, et k&otilde;nealusel isikul on vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi oma kodanikelt n&otilde;utavatega v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsed erialased teadmised, pidades silmas ohtlikku m&otilde;ju, mida toksilised tooted v&otilde;ivad keskkonna kaudu kas otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt avaldada inimeste, loomade ja taimede tervisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the different characteristics of toxic products and of their varying degrees of toxicity with respect to human, animal and plant health, knowledge of the effects of any one of these products or experience in handling it cannot reasonably be considered as proof of equivalent competence for the distribution or professional use of other such products or all such products; whereas, therefore, the host Member State must have the power to limit the scope of the transitional measures to products which consist of the same active materials or which have similar effects on human, animal and plant health, either directly or indirectly through the environment; </inglise>
<eesti> pidades silmas toksiliste toodete mitmesuguseid omadusi ja nende toksilisuse erinevat m&auml;&auml;ra inimeste, loomade ja taimede tervisele, ei saa p&otilde;hjendatult lugeda teadmisi &uuml;he sellise toote m&otilde;just v&otilde;i kogemusi selle k&auml;sitsemisel t&otilde;enduseks, nagu oleks olemas samav&auml;&auml;rne p&auml;devus muude selliste toodete v&otilde;i k&otilde;igi selliste toodete turustamiseks v&otilde;i erialaseks kasutamiseks; seet&otilde;ttu peab vastuv&otilde;tval liikmesriigil olema &otilde;igus piirata &uuml;leminekumeetmete reguleerimisala toodetega, mis koosnevad &uuml;hesugustest toimeainetest v&otilde;i millel on keskkonna kaudu otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt inimeste, loomade ja taimede tervisele sarnane m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in so far as in Member States the taking up or pursuit of the activity in question is also dependent in the case of paid employees on the possession of general, commercial or professional knowledge or ability, this Directive should also apply to this category of persons in order to remove an obstacle to the free movement of workers and thereby to supplement the measures adopted in Council Regulation (EEC) No 1612/68 (1) of 15 October 1968 on freedom of movement for workers within the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> niiv&otilde;rd kui palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajatel peavad liikmesriikides k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse alustamiseks v&otilde;i j&auml;tkamiseks olema &uuml;ld-, majandus- v&otilde;i erialased teadmised v&otilde;i oskused, tuleks k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldada ka k&otilde;nealuste isikute kategooria suhtes, et k&otilde;rvaldada t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u vaba liikumise takistus ja t&auml;iendada seega meetmeid, mis on vastu v&otilde;etud n&otilde;ukogu 15. oktoobri 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1612/68 t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vaba liikumise kohta &uuml;henduses (6); </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the same reason, the provisions laid down in respect of proof of good repute and proof of no previous bankruptcy should also be applicable to paid employees; </inglise>
<eesti> samal p&otilde;hjusel tuleks palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes kohaldada s&auml;tteid, mis reguleerivad hea maine ja varasema pankroti puudumise t&otilde;endamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the main purpose of the measures provided for in this Directive will disappear once the coordination of conditions for the taking up and pursuit of the activities in question and the mutual recognition of diplomas, certificates and other formal qualifications have been achieved, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga s&auml;testatud meetmete peamine eesm&auml;rk kaob, kui saavutatakse k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste alustamise ja j&auml;tkamise tingimuste koosk&otilde;lastamine ning diplomite, t&otilde;endite ja muude kvalifikatsioonitunnistuste vastastikune tunnustamine, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
