<inglise> The transitional measures shall also apply to persons pursuing as paid employees the activities referred to in paragraph 2, as shall Article 7 (1) to (4), of Council Directive No 74/557/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekumeetmeid, nii nagu ka n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi nr 74/557/EM&Uuml; artikli 7 l&otilde;ikeid 1-4, kohaldatakse samuti isikute suhtes, kes palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajatena j&auml;tkavad l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tegevusi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Where, in a Member State, the taking up or pursuit of any activity referred to in the first subparagraph of Article 1 (2), is dependent on the possession of general, commercial or professional knowledge and ability, that Member State shall accept as sufficient evidence of such knowledge and ability the fact that the activity in question has been pursued in another Member State for any of the following periods: (a) five consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity, such activity not having ceased more than two years before the date when the application referred to in Article 4 (2) is made; </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud kutsealal tegutsema asumiseks v&otilde;i tegutsemiseks peavad liikmesriigis olema &uuml;ld-, majandus- v&otilde;i kutsealased teadmised ja -oskused, aktsepteerib k&otilde;nealune liikmesriik selliste teadmiste ja oskuste piisava t&otilde;endusena asjaolu, et k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal on tegutsetud teises liikmesriigis &uuml;hel j&auml;rgmistest ajavahemikest: a) viis j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui see tegevus ei l&otilde;ppenud varem kui kaks aastat enne artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud taotluse tegemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) two consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity where the beneficiary possesses a certificate of ability and competence for the activity in question authorizing him to pursue the activities of trade in or distribution of toxic products in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence he comes; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kaks j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui kasusaajal on k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse kohta sertifikaat, mis t&otilde;endab tema oskusi ja p&auml;devust ja mis lubab tal j&auml;tkata toksiliste toodetega kauplemist v&otilde;i toksiliste toodete vahendamist p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust ta tuleb; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) three consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity where the beneficiary proves that for the activity in question he has received previous training attested by a certificate recognized by the State or regarded by the competent professional or trade body as fully satisfying its requirements; </inglise>
<eesti> c) kolm j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui soodustatud isik t&otilde;endab, et ta on enne seda saanud k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe, mille kohta tal on riiklikult tunnustatud v&otilde;i p&auml;deva kutse- v&otilde;i majandusorganisatsiooni poolt oma n&otilde;uetele t&auml;ielikult vastavaks tunnistatud tunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) three consecutive years in a non-independent capacity where the beneficiary possesses a certificate of ability and competence for the activity in question authorizing him to pursue the activities of trade in or distribution of toxic products in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence he comes; </inglise>
<eesti> d) kolm j&auml;rjestikust aastat palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajana, kui kasusaajal on k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse kohta sertifikaat, mis t&otilde;endab tema oskusi ja p&auml;devust ja mis lubab tal j&auml;tkata toksiliste toodetega kauplemist v&otilde;i toksiliste toodete vahendamist p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust ta tuleb; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) four consecutive years in a non-independent capacity where the beneficiary proves that for the activity in question he has received previous training, attested by a certificate recognized by the State or regarded by the competent professional or trade body as fully satisfying its requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> e) neli j&auml;rjestikust aastat palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajana, kui kasusaaja t&otilde;endab, et ta on enne seda saanud k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe, mille kohta tal on riiklikult tunnustatud v&otilde;i p&auml;deva kutse- v&otilde;i majandusorganisatsiooni poolt oma n&otilde;uetele t&auml;ielikult vastavaks tunnistatud tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise> This Article only relates to trade in or distribution of packaged toxic products intended for delivery to the final user in their original packaging. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev artikkel k&auml;sitleb ainult l&otilde;pptarbijale originaalpakendis tarnimiseks m&otilde;eldud pakendatud toksiliste toodetega kauplemist v&otilde;i nende turustamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Where, in a Member State, the taking up or pursuit of any activity referred to in the second subparagraph of Article 1 (2) is dependent on the possession of general, commercial, or professional knowledge and ability, that Member State shall accept as sufficient evidence of such knowledge and ability the fact that the activity in question has been pursued in another Member State for any of the following periods: (a) six consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity such activity not having ceased more than two years before the date when the application referred to in Article 4 (2) is made; </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 teises l&otilde;igus nimetatud kutsealal tegutsema asumiseks v&otilde;i tegutsemiseks peavad liikmesriigis olema &uuml;ld-, majandus- v&otilde;i kutsealased teadmised ja -oskused, aktsepteerib k&otilde;nealune liikmesriik selliste teadmiste ja oskuste piisava t&otilde;endusena asjaolu, et k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal on tegutsetud teises liikmesriigis &uuml;hel j&auml;rgmistest ajavahemikest: a) kuus j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui see tegevus ei l&otilde;ppenud varem kui kaks aastat enne artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud taotluse tegemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) three consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity where the beneficiary possesses a certificate of ability and competence for the activity in question authorizing him to pursue activities entailing the professional use of toxic products in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence he comes; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kolm j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui kasusaajal on k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse kohta sertifikaat, mis t&otilde;endab tema oskusi ja p&auml;devust ja lubab tal j&auml;tkata toksiliste toodete erialast kasutamist n&otilde;udvaid tegevusi p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust ta tuleb; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) four consecutive years in an independent capacity or in a managerial capacity where the beneficiary proves that for the activity in question he has received previous training, attested by a certificate recognized by the State or regarded by the competent professional or trade body as fully satisfying its requirements; </inglise>
<eesti> c) neli j&auml;rjestikust aastat s&otilde;ltumatult v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhina, kui kasusaaja t&otilde;endab, et ta on enne seda saanud k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe, mille kohta tal on riiklikult tunnustatud v&otilde;i p&auml;deva kutse- v&otilde;i majandusorganisatsiooni poolt oma n&otilde;uetele t&auml;ielikult vastavaks tunnistatud tunnistus; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) four consecutive years in a non-independent capacity where the beneficiary possesses a certificate of ability and competence for the activity in question authorizing him to pursue activities entailing the professional use of toxic products in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence he comes; </inglise>
<eesti> d) neli j&auml;rjestikust aastat palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajana, kui kasusaajal on k&otilde;nealuse tegevuse kohta sertifikaat, mis t&otilde;endab tema oskusi ja p&auml;devust ja lubab tal j&auml;tkata toksiliste toodete erialast kasutamist n&otilde;udvaid tegevusi p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust ta tuleb; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) five consecutive years in a non-independent capacity where the beneficiary proves that for the activity in question he has received previous training, attested by a certificate recognized by the State or regarded by the competent professional or trade body as fully satisfying its requirements; </inglise>
<eesti> e) viis j&auml;rjestikust aastat palgat&ouml;&ouml;tajana, kui kasusaaja t&otilde;endab, et ta on enne seda saanud k&otilde;nealusel kutsealal v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe, mille kohta tal on riiklikult tunnustatud v&otilde;i p&auml;deva kutse- v&otilde;i majandusorganisatsiooni poolt oma n&otilde;uetele t&auml;ielikult vastavaks tunnistatud tunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions in (a), (c) and (e) are not applicable to activities entailing the professional use of certain highly toxic products given below: </inglise>
<eesti> Punktide a, c ja e s&auml;tteid ei kohaldata tegevuste suhtes, mis eeldavad teatavate j&auml;rgnevate, eriti toksiliste toodete erialast kasutamist: </eesti>
<inglise> - Hydrocyanic acid and its soluble salts, </inglise>
<eesti> - Vesinikts&uuml;aniidhape ja selle lahustuvad soolad, </eesti>
<inglise> - Hydrofluoric acid and its soluble salts, </inglise>
<eesti> - Vesinikfluoriidhape ja selle lahustuvad soolad, </eesti>
<inglise> - Acrylonitrile, </inglise>
<eesti> - Akr&uuml;&uuml;lnitriil, </eesti>
<inglise> - Liquid compressed ammonium, </inglise>
<eesti> - Vedel suruammoonium, </eesti>
<inglise> - Methyl bromide, </inglise>
<eesti> - Met&uuml;&uuml;lbromiid, </eesti>
<inglise> - Chloropicrin, </inglise>
<eesti> - Kloorpikriin, </eesti>
<inglise> - Hydrogen phosphide and products liable to liberate it, </inglise>
<eesti> - Vesinikfosfiid ja seda vabastada v&otilde;ivad tooted, </eesti>
<inglise> - Ethylene oxide, </inglise>
<eesti> - Et&uuml;leenoksiid, </eesti>
<inglise> - Carbon disulphide, </inglise>
<eesti> - S&uuml;sinikdisulfiid, </eesti>
<inglise> - Carbon tetrachloride, </inglise>
<eesti> - S&uuml;siniktetrakloriid, </eesti>
<inglise> - Trichloroacetronitrile. </inglise>
<eesti> - Trikloroatsetonitriil. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of applying the provisions in (b) and (d) to these highly toxic products, the certificate of ability and competence must state the product or products which the beneficiary is authorized to use in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence he comes. </inglise>
<eesti> Punktide b ja d s&auml;tete kohaldamisel nende v&auml;ga toksiliste toodete suhtes peavad oskuste v&otilde;i p&auml;devuse kohta antud sertifikaadis olema nimetatud toode v&otilde;i tooted, mida kasusaajal on &otilde;igus kasutada p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust ta tuleb. </eesti>
<inglise> In this case, the beneficiary's activity shall not have ceased more than two years before the date when the application referred to in Article 4 (2) is made. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul ei tohi kasusaaja tegevus olla l&otilde;ppenud varem kui kaks aastat enne artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud taotluse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A person shall be regarded as having pursued an activity in a managerial capacity within the meaning of Articles 2 and 3 if he has pursued such an activity in an industrial or commercial undertaking in the occupational field in question: (a) as manager of an undertaking or manager of a branch of an undertaking; or </inglise>
<eesti> Isikut k&auml;sitletakse ettev&otilde;tte juhina tegutsenud isikuna artiklite 2 ja 3 t&auml;henduses, kui ta on asjakohasel kutsealal tegutsenud t&ouml;&ouml;stus- v&otilde;i &auml;riettev&otilde;ttes: a) ettev&otilde;tte juhina v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte filiaali juhina, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) as deputy to the proprietor or to the manager of an undertaking, where such post involves responsibility equivalent to that of the proprietor or manager represented; or </inglise>
<eesti> b) ettev&otilde;tte juhina v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte juhi aset&auml;itjana, kui selline ametikoht eeldab esindatava omaniku v&otilde;i juhiga samav&auml;&auml;rset vastutust; v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (c) in a managerial post with duties relating to trade in or distribution of toxic products and with responsibility for at least one department of the undertaking, or in a managerial post with responsibility for the use of the said products. </inglise>
<eesti> c) juhtival ametikohal, mille kohustused seostuvad toksiliste toodetega kauplemise v&otilde;i toksiliste toodete vahendamisega ja vastutust v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tte osakonna eest, v&otilde;i juhtival ametikohal koos vastutusega nimetatud toodete kasutamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Proof that the conditions laid down in Articles 2 and 3 are satisfied shall be established by an attestation issued by the competent authority or body in the Member State of origin or Member State whence the person concerned comes, which the latter shall submit in support of his application for authorization to pursue the activity or activities in question in the host Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> T&otilde;estuse, et artiklites 2 ja 3 etten&auml;htud tingimused on t&auml;idetud, annab t&otilde;end, mille v&auml;ljastab p&auml;dev asutus v&otilde;i organ p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust k&otilde;nealune isik tuleb, ja mille isik esitab oma taotluse t&otilde;enduseks, et j&auml;tkata k&otilde;nealust tegevust v&otilde;i tegevusi vastuv&otilde;tvates liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Such attestation shall state, where appropriate, whether, in the Member State of origin or Member State whence the person concerned comes, authorization is limited to the taking up of activities relating to the distribution of toxic products or to activities entailing the professional use of such products, or whether certain toxic products are excluded from these latter activities. </inglise>
<eesti> Selles t&otilde;endis on vajaduse korral nimetatud, kas luba on p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i riigis, kust k&otilde;nealune isik tuleb, piiratud toksiliste toodete vahendamisega seotud tegevuste v&otilde;i selliste toodete erialast kasutamist eeldavate tegevuste alustamisega, v&otilde;i kas nendest tegevustest on v&auml;lja arvatud teatavad toksilised tooted. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall, within the time limit laid down in Article 7, designate the authorities and bodies competent to issue the certificates referred to in paragraph 2 and shall forthwith inform the other Member States and the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid m&auml;&auml;ravad artiklis 7 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul asutused ja organid, kellel on &otilde;igus l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud t&otilde;endeid v&auml;lja anda, ning teatavad sellest viivitamata teistele liikmesriikidele ja komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Where, in the Member State of origin or the Member State whence the person concerned comes, the formal qualifications laid down in Articles 2 and 3 or the attestations laid down in Article 4 (2) authorize only the taking up of activities relating to the distribution of toxic products or of activities entailing the professional use of such products, or exclude certain toxic products from these latter activities, the host Member State may apply the same limitations in its territory and also exclude from activities entailing the professional use of toxic products consisting of the same active material as products excluded by formal qualifications and attestations or involving similar risks for human, animal and plant health either directly or indirectly through the environment. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis v&otilde;i liikmesriigis, kust k&otilde;nealune isik tuleb, lubavad artiklites 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud kvalifikatsioonit&otilde;endid v&otilde;i artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud tunnistused ainult toksiliste toodete vahendamisega seotud tegevuste v&otilde;i selliste toodete erialast kasutamist eeldavate tegevuste alustamist v&otilde;i arvavad nende tegevuste hulgast v&auml;lja teatavad toksilised tooted, v&otilde;ib vastuv&otilde;ttev liikmesriik oma territooriumil kohaldada samu piiranguid ning samuti arvata toksiliste toodete erialast kasutamist eeldavate tegevuste hulgast v&auml;lja tooted, mis sisaldavad sama toimeainet kui v&auml;ljaarvatud tooted v&otilde;i ohustavad samamoodi keskkonna kaudu kas otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt inimeste, loomade ja taimede tervist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall remain applicable until the entry into force of provisions relating to the coordination of national rules concerning the taking up and pursuit of the activities in question. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse kuni k&otilde;nealuste tegevuste alustamist ja j&auml;tkamist k&auml;sitlevate siseriiklike eeskirjade koosk&otilde;lastamist k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete j&otilde;ustumiseni. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the measures necessary to comply with this Directive within six months of its notification and shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;itmiseks vajalikud meetmed kuue kuu jooksul alates direktiivi teatavakstegemisest ning teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall communicate to the Commission the texts of the main provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive, the Commission shall inform the other Member States thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastuv&otilde;etavate p&otilde;hiliste siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide teksti ja komisjon teatab sellest teistele liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 4 June 1974. </inglise>
